  "target_response": {
    "text": "Strain is her watch's way of scoring how much cardiovascular work a day contained — it accumulates from how long and how high the heart rate is pushed, so a long run scores far more than a stroll. It's a load measure, not a fitness grade, and it only rises; recovering well shows up elsewhere. You don't have one because strain needs continuous heart-rate data, and your setup is manual logging — last night's 7.0 hours of sleep is the only measurement recorded, so there's nothing for me to compute it from. If you want a stand-in, rating each workout's effort from easy to maximal right after finishing tracks weekly load surprisingly well.",
